  "texts": [
    "presented a generative adversarial network (GAN) for image super resolution (SR) using a perceptual loss function with adversarial and content losses in SRGAN [23].",
    "The adversarial loss pushes our solution to the natural picture manifold using a discriminator network trained to distinguish super-resolved images from photo-realistic images.",
    "suggest CoGAN [24] for learning multi-domain picture distributions.",
    "CoGAN can learn a joint distribution without tuples of corresponding images in separate domains, unlike other methods.",
    "Karras et al. [25] offer a new approach to training generative adversarial networks called Progressive Growing GAN."
  ],
